            gaseous fuel, such as in the production of chemicals, petrochemicals, or other industrial materials.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Power generation: </strong>Gas vaporizers are used to convert liquid natural gas (LNG) into a
            gaseous state so it can be used to power electric generators.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Medical/Pharmaceutical: </strong>They are also used in medical and pharmaceutical applications
            where liquid gases like Oxygen and Nitrogen are vaporized and delivered to patients through breathing
            apparatus.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Refrigeration: </strong>Gas vaporizers are used to convert liquid refrigerants, such as propane or
            ammonia, into a gaseous state so that it can be used to cool and refrigerate.
        </li>
    </ul>
